# Acceptance Criteria: Code Review

Stitch must complete all criteria before the review is considered done.

## Review Completeness

- [ ] All changed files have been analyzed
- [ ] PR description and context understood
- [ ] Each code change evaluated for correctness, security, and maintainability

## Feedback Posted

- [ ] Review comments posted to GitHub PR
- [ ] Overall review verdict submitted (approve/request changes/comment)
- [ ] Critical issues flagged as blocking (if any)
- [ ] Suggestions formatted with clear file:line references

## Quality Checks

- [ ] Security vulnerabilities identified and noted
- [ ] Performance concerns documented (if any)
- [ ] Test coverage gaps mentioned (if applicable)
- [ ] Code style consistency checked

## Completion

- [ ] GitHub review status updated (APPROVED, CHANGES_REQUESTED, or COMMENTED)
- [ ] All review comments successfully posted
